QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Directly picked in before the conveyor belt or in the gear

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Start of sorting
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Picked of the conveyor belt at the start of sorting

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Middle of sorting
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Picked of the conveyor belt at the middle of sorting

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: End of sorting
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Picked of the conveyor belt at the end of sorting

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: A
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Excellent condition
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Fish in excellent condition, vigorous body movement and no or minor external injuries only

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: B
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Good condition
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Fish in good condition, weak body movement, minor external injuries

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: C
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Poor condition
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Fish in poor condition, no body movement but fish can move operculum and minor or major external injuries

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: B
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: BMS Landings
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Landings below minimum conservation reference size, BMS. Relevant for stocks under the landing obligation. The BMS landing will consist of BMS landings and predator damaged fish.

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: D
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Discards
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: The part of the catch which is thrown overboard into the sea and not registered in the logbook. This is still based on fishery observer estimations and apply to all stocks, both under and out of the landing obligation.

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: R
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Logbook Registered Discard
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Relevant for stocks under landing obligation. Logbook registered discard are discards, which are registered in the logbook and are under the exemption rules (e.g. de minimis). Damaged fish can be included under this Logbook registered discard.

QUALITATIVE_VALUE.LABEL: C
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.NAME: Catch
QUALITATIVE_VALUE.DESCRIPTION: Catch can be used for a few species, for which there is no separation in the information of landings or discards
